# CSVParserTool — core

## Stack

- **.NET Framework 4.8.1**, **Windows Forms** (`WinExe`), **C#** (LangVersion preview in csproj).
- **Solution**: `CSVParserTool.slnx`; main UI: `Form1` via `Program.cs`.

## Architecture (short)

- `Form1` owns: a single **project root** path (do **not** include `Assets` in the picker — the tool prepends `{root}/Assets/…`), the XLSX source folder, XLSX list + preview, logging, and `FileSystemWatcher` on the XLSX folder.
- **Data export**: 디스크 `Assets/_Game/DataTables/Content/CSV|Bytes`; Addressables 주소 `Content/CSV/DT_*.csv`, `Content/Bytes/DT_*.bytes`. **`.cs`** → `DataTables/Scripts`.
- User settings: `Properties/Settings` (`ProjectRootPath`, `ExcelSourceFolderPath`).

## Editing conventions

- Keep changes **scoped** to the request; avoid drive-by refactors across unrelated files.
- **Partial forms**: logic in `Form1.cs`; controls/layout in `Form1.Designer.cs` (designer-generated — extend via Visual Studio designer when possible).
- **UI copy** may stay in Korean in the app; stay consistent with existing tone in the same control/feature.
- Reuse existing patterns (`AddLog`, `CheckDataSettingAvailable`, path helpers) instead of duplicating logic.

## Namespaces

- App code: `CSVParserTool` (e.g. `Form1`, `LogLevel`).
- Generated Unity table rows are plain **`PJDev.Data`** POCOs with **`public int Id`** (no `IDataRecord`). Do not rename this namespace in generated strings without updating Unity consumers.
